						               													<description>The Turbulent 60's and The End Game, take Bruce Costello's popular simulation of the Cold War turning hot, Warplan Dropshot from the 50's to the 60's and 70's-90's.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dropshot II: The Turbulent 60's scenarios: In the &amp;quot;Berlin, 1961&amp;quot; World War III starts at the Berlin Wall. In &amp;quot;The Cuban Missile Crisis, 1962&amp;quot; what almost happened happens. In &amp;quot;The Six Day War,&amp;quot; an accident in the Mediterranean sparks the big one in 1967. In The Czechoslovakian Crisis, 1968&amp;quot; Soviet and NATO clashes escalate into total war. &amp;quot;Border War in the Far East, 1969&amp;quot; has the US getting involved in a nuclear war between China and Russia.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dropshot III: The End Game scenarios: In &amp;quot;Middle East, 1973&amp;quot; the US and the Soviet Union get too involved with the Yom Kippur War. In &amp;quot;1976 - Bolt from the Blue&amp;quot; Kremlin hardliners opt for a preemptive war while everyone is taking d&amp;eacute;tente. &amp;quot;December Surprise - Iran, 1979&amp;quot; has President Carter invading Iran and the Soviets having to react. In &amp;quot;Solidarity - Poland, 1981&amp;quot; the labor movement is crushed and the West reacts. In &amp;quot;Deep Paranoia&amp;quot; a NATO exercise pushes the Soviets too far. &amp;quot;Hardliners Last Gasp, 1987&amp;quot; supposes an alternative end to the Cold War.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;400 km/hex on strategic map and 75 km/hex on map of Europe, 2 months/turn, armies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a DTP game with die-cut counters. Two 8.5x11 inch strategic hemispheric maps, one 11x17 inch map of Europe, 616 counters, play aids, charts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Warplan: Dropshot II/III was a nominee in the Charles S. Roberts awards for Best Modern Era Boardgame (Charles S. Roberts Awards) for 2005.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
